WEBVTT

00:03.124 --> 00:04.795
[ PHARRELL WILLIAMS'
"HAPPY" PLAYS ]

00:04.795 --> 00:07.048
Meredith:
EVERY SURGEON IS TRAINED
TO LOOK FOR PROBLEMS.

00:07.048 --> 00:09.590
TO LOOK AT A PERSON AND SAY,
"WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?"

00:09.590 --> 00:11.802
WHERE AM I SUPPOSED
TO BE NOW?

00:11.802 --> 00:13.224
Woman:
YOU CAN COME WITH ME.

00:13.224 --> 00:14.935
CROSS.

00:14.935 --> 00:15.766
DRUNK OR DERANGED.

00:15.766 --> 00:17.558
FIND OUT WHICH.

00:17.558 --> 00:19.600
SIR. HI.

00:19.600 --> 00:20.941
UH, CAN I HELP YOU?

00:20.941 --> 00:23.274
I-I-I DON'T KNOW.

00:23.274 --> 00:25.106
YOU GUYS CALLED ME.

00:25.106 --> 00:26.647
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

00:26.647 --> 00:27.648
♪ BECAUSE I'M HAPPY ♪

00:27.648 --> 00:29.150
WE'RE TRAINED TO FORESEE

00:29.150 --> 00:30.611
THE UGLIEST POSSIBLE OUTCOME.

00:30.611 --> 00:32.363
SHE ACTUALLY SAID --

00:32.363 --> 00:35.616
STEPH SAID I'M NOT AS GOOD
A SURGEON AS SHE IS.

00:35.616 --> 00:37.288
IS THAT TRUE?

00:37.288 --> 00:38.289
OF COURSE NOT.

00:38.289 --> 00:40.081
YEAH,
BUT IS THAT THE PERCEPTION?

00:40.081 --> 00:42.333
DO ATTENDINGS JUST AUTOMATICALLY
GO TO ANYONE BUT ME?

00:42.333 --> 00:44.835
I THINK YOU'RE AMAZING.

00:44.835 --> 00:46.757
♪ BECAUSE I'M HAPPY ♪

00:46.757 --> 00:48.929
♪ CLAP ALONG IF YOU FEEL
LIKE THAT'S WHAT YOU WANNA DO ♪

00:48.929 --> 00:50.931
[ CELLPHONE CHIMES, BUZZES ]

00:50.931 --> 00:52.723
OH, MY GOD.

00:52.723 --> 00:54.595
OH, MY GOD!
MR. JAFFEE!

00:54.595 --> 00:57.017
WHEN YOUR JOB
IS TO MAKE PEOPLE BETTER,

00:57.017 --> 00:59.810
YOU'RE AUTOMATICALLY INCLINED
TO LOOK FOR THE WORST IN THEM.
[ CELLPHONE CHIRPING ]

01:01.732 --> 01:03.734
WILSON, I HAVE THREE KIDS.

01:03.734 --> 01:05.236
THREE.

01:05.236 --> 01:07.398
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
HOW LITTLE SLEEP I GET?

01:07.398 --> 01:09.400
♪♪

01:09.400 --> 01:11.572
MR. JAFFEE?

01:11.572 --> 01:13.154
MM.
ARE YOU SURE
YOU DON'T WANT TO JUST SLEEP?

01:13.154 --> 01:14.745
[ GIGGLES ]

01:14.745 --> 01:16.247
YOU CANNOT KEEP THIS UP.

01:16.247 --> 01:17.698
GREY IS KILLING YOU.

01:17.698 --> 01:21.202
I KNOW, BUT I CAN'T THINK
OF THAT RIGHT NOW.

01:21.202 --> 01:22.833
'CAUSE RIGHT NOW,
I'M IN A BED.

01:22.833 --> 01:27.047
A COMFY, COMFY BED...

01:27.047 --> 01:28.799
WITH YOU.

01:28.799 --> 01:32.843
♪ CLAP ALONG IF YOU FEEL
LIKE A ROOM WITHOUT A ROOF ♪

01:32.843 --> 01:35.216
♪ BECAUSE I'M HAPPY ♪
DID YOU JUST FALL ASLEEP?

01:35.216 --> 01:37.057
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]
GOT IT!

01:37.057 --> 01:38.269
WHA-- [ GROANS ]

01:38.269 --> 01:40.271
HELLO?
UH-HUH.

01:41.562 --> 01:43.023
OF COURSE IT IS.

01:43.023 --> 01:44.775
YEAH.
OF COURSE IT IS.

01:44.775 --> 01:46.397
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.

01:46.397 --> 01:47.988
NO, ABSOLUTELY.
ABSOLUTELY I CAN.

01:47.988 --> 01:49.900
UH-HUH.
NO, OF COURSE.

01:49.900 --> 01:51.782
WHO'S MR. JAFFEE?

01:51.782 --> 01:54.405
SIMON JAFFEE.
END-STAGE RENAL DISEASE.

01:54.405 --> 01:56.697
HE'S BEEN ON DIALYSIS
FOR THE LAST 18 MONTHS

01:56.697 --> 01:57.998
WAITING
FOR A TRANSPLANT DONOR.

01:57.998 --> 01:58.999
WHY SO LONG?

01:58.999 --> 02:00.241
ANTIBODIES.

02:00.241 --> 02:01.542
HE NEEDS
A SIX-ANTIGEN MATCH --

02:01.542 --> 02:03.834
AN IMPOSSIBLE MATCH
UNTIL TONIGHT.

02:03.834 --> 02:05.296
IT'S -- WE'VE BEEN
LOOKING FOREVER.

02:05.296 --> 02:06.917
IT'S LIKE FINDING
THE HOLY GRAIL.

02:06.917 --> 02:09.129
BLAKE, WHEN WAS MR. JAFFEE'S
LAST ROUND OF DIALYSIS?

02:09.129 --> 02:11.172
OH, UM, LOOKING...

02:11.172 --> 02:13.424
HE WAS AT THE DIALYSIS CENTER
TWO DAYS AGO.

02:13.424 --> 02:16.927
ELECTROLYTES AND RENAL LABS WERE
WITHIN EXPECTED LIMITS, SO...

02:16.927 --> 02:18.679
I'VE BEEN ON HIS CASE
SINCE I WAS AN INTERN.

02:18.679 --> 02:21.021
I'M SO SORRY, DR. GREY.
I WILL CATCH UP.

02:21.021 --> 02:22.062
IT'S OKAY, BLAKE.

02:22.062 --> 02:23.524
DO THE BEST YOU CAN,

02:23.524 --> 02:25.476
AND ASK WILSON
IF YOU HAVE ANY QUESTIONS.

02:27.067 --> 02:28.609
OH, THERE ARE MY GIRLS.
[ CHUCKLES ]

02:28.609 --> 02:30.401
MR. JAFFEE,
IT'S SO GOOD TO SEE YOU.

02:30.401 --> 02:31.652
WHERE ARE THE GRANDKIDS?

02:31.652 --> 02:33.904
I HAVEN'T EVEN
CALLED THEM YET.

02:33.904 --> 02:37.278
I-I-I WANTED TO WAIT UNTIL
I KNEW IT WAS A SURE THING.

02:37.278 --> 02:38.779
SO...

02:38.779 --> 02:39.910
IS IT TRUE?

02:39.910 --> 02:41.492
IT'S TRUE.
[ CHUCKLES ]

02:41.492 --> 02:42.543
WE FOUND YOU A KIDNEY.

02:42.543 --> 02:43.994
[ CRIES ]

02:46.457 --> 02:47.958
[ CHUCKLES ]

02:47.958 --> 02:49.960
[ SIREN WAILS IN DISTANCE ]

02:49.960 --> 02:51.342
THANKS AGAIN
FOR BREAKFAST.

02:51.342 --> 02:54.215
MY PLEASURE.

02:54.215 --> 02:56.967
THIS WAS HIS LAST NIGHT
IN MY HOUSE.

02:56.967 --> 02:58.639
YOU JUST MADE THE MAN
PANCAKES.

02:58.639 --> 03:01.222
BECAUSE I AM A BENEVOLENT LEADER
AND GOOD HOST.

03:01.222 --> 03:03.013
AND I'VE BEEN WAITING FOR
THIS THING TO RESOLVE ITSELF.

03:03.013 --> 03:04.935
IT HAS NOT.

03:04.935 --> 03:06.517
THIS JOB IS STRESSFUL.

03:06.517 --> 03:08.809
I NEED TO GO HOME AT NIGHT
AND BE ALONE WITH MY HUSBAND.

03:08.809 --> 03:10.110
WELL, I-I AGREE WITH THAT,

03:10.110 --> 03:11.442
BUT -- BUT --
DA-UH!

03:11.442 --> 03:12.693
MIRANDA, HE 'S MY FRIEND,
ALL RIGHT?

03:12.693 --> 03:13.904
AND HE'S MY BOSS.

03:13.904 --> 03:15.446
I'M YOUR BOSS, TOO.
AND HIS BOSS.

03:15.446 --> 03:16.817
I'M ALL YOUR BOSSES.

03:16.817 --> 03:19.740
IF YOU WANT YOUR WIFE BACK,
TAKE CARE OF YOUR BUSINESS...

03:19.740 --> 03:22.583
TODAY.

03:22.583 --> 03:24.084
SO, I'M JUST WONDERING
IF MAYBE WE SHOULD RETHINK

03:24.084 --> 03:26.247
THE RESIDENT-ROTATION
SYSTEM.

03:26.247 --> 03:27.458
I MEAN,
MAKE SURE THAT OUR RESIDENTS

03:27.458 --> 03:29.920
GET AN EQUAL OPPORTUNITY
ON EVERY SPECIALTY.

03:29.920 --> 03:31.292
ISN'T THAT HAPPENING?

03:31.292 --> 03:33.043
WELL, THERE'S A DANGER
THAT OUR RESIDENTS

03:33.043 --> 03:34.635
ARE BEING MONOPOLIZED
BY A SINGLE ATTENDING.

03:34.635 --> 03:36.387
SHE'S TALKING ABOUT BLAKE.
YOU KNOW WHAT?

03:36.387 --> 03:37.968
THIS IS NOT YOUR BUSI--
ISN'T BLAKE WITH GREY?

03:37.968 --> 03:39.720
YES, AND SHE HAS BEEN
SINCE SHE GOT HERE.

03:39.720 --> 03:41.642
I WORRY SHE'S NOT GETTING
A FULL EDUCATION.

03:41.642 --> 03:44.224
AND GREY IS --
[ SCOFFS ]

03:44.224 --> 03:46.347
SHE'S --
SHE'S RUNNING HER RAGGED.

03:46.347 --> 03:48.269
RESIDENCY RUNS YOU RAGGED.

03:48.269 --> 03:50.561
WE'VE ALL BEEN THERE, TORRES.
YOU KNOW THIS AS WELL AS ANYONE.

03:50.561 --> 03:51.902
NO, BUT THIS IS DIFFERENT.
THIS IS DIFFERENT.

03:51.902 --> 03:53.153
I THINK IT'S PERSONAL.

03:53.153 --> 03:54.985
IS IT THAT YOU WANT
TO SPEND

03:54.985 --> 03:56.236
MORE TIME
WITH YOUR GIRLFRIEND?

03:56.236 --> 03:57.908
AMELIA,
COULD YOU PLEASE --

03:57.908 --> 03:59.570
I MEAN, YOU ARE SAYING
THAT IT'S PERSONAL.

03:59.570 --> 04:00.951
HEY, HEY --
ALL RIGHT. ALL RIGHT.

04:02.533 --> 04:06.787
HAS BLAKE EXPRESSED
THIS CONCERN OR JUST YOU?

04:06.787 --> 04:07.918
OKAY.
SHE'S --

04:07.918 --> 04:08.999
BLAKE STAYS WITH GREY.

04:08.999 --> 04:10.080
[ SIGHS ]
WE DON'T HAVE A POLICY

04:10.080 --> 04:11.502
TO MOVE AROUND RESIDENTS

04:11.502 --> 04:12.833
TO ACCOMMODATE
YOUR PERSONAL LIVES.

04:12.833 --> 04:14.084
NO, THAT'S NOT
WHAT I WAS SAYING.

04:14.084 --> 04:15.756
IF BLAKE HAS A PROBLEM,
SHE COMES TO ME.

04:15.756 --> 04:18.008
[ SCOFFS ]

04:20.010 --> 04:21.842
[ WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER P.A. SYSTEM ]

04:21.842 --> 04:23.844
Woman: ALL RIGHT.
HE HAS ALREADY BEEN SEEN.

04:23.844 --> 04:25.346
I KNOW THE DOCTOR IS...

04:25.346 --> 04:26.647
[ New Zealand accent ]
HEY, ALL.

04:26.647 --> 04:28.689
UH, I WAS JUST WONDERING

04:28.689 --> 04:31.352
IF SOMEONE COULD TELL ME
WHERE I CAN GET SOME SCRUBS.

04:31.352 --> 04:34.445
UH...THIRD FLOOR
BY THE DISPENSARY.

04:34.445 --> 04:36.106
CHEERS.

04:36.106 --> 04:37.448
YOU'RE, UH,
DR. PIERCE, RIGHT?

04:37.448 --> 04:38.399
MM-HMM.

04:38.399 --> 04:39.570
YEAH,
I-I JUST WANTED TO SAY

04:39.570 --> 04:41.362
I'M SUPER EXCITED,

04:41.362 --> 04:43.163
AND I CAN'T WAIT
TO GET STARTED.

04:44.575 --> 04:45.576
GREAT.

04:45.576 --> 04:47.368
♪♪

04:47.368 --> 04:50.210
GO GET 'EM.

04:52.172 --> 04:55.175
OKEYDOKEY.

04:56.587 --> 04:57.718
YEP.

04:59.510 --> 05:00.471
WHO WAS THAT?

05:01.592 --> 05:02.843
[ Mumbling ]
I DON'T KNOW.

05:13.854 --> 05:16.357
[ GRUNTS ]

05:16.357 --> 05:17.398
OH.

05:17.398 --> 05:18.609
OH, HEY.

05:18.609 --> 05:19.860
I FOUND YOU.

05:19.860 --> 05:22.322
PULLED A NIGHT SHIFT.

05:22.322 --> 05:24.865
THIS IS A NICE WAY
TO WAKE UP.

05:24.865 --> 05:27.117
I COULD GET USED TO THIS.

05:27.117 --> 05:29.660
[ SIGHS ]
HOW'S YOUR DAY?

05:31.582 --> 05:34.505
I HAD TO LISTEN TO TORRES GO ON
AND ON ABOUT HER GIRLFRIEND,

05:34.505 --> 05:40.381
WHO MEREDITH'S GOT BASICALLY
CHAINED TO HER SERVICE.

05:40.381 --> 05:42.132
I DON'T KNOW
HOW SHE EVEN LOOKS AT HER.

05:47.928 --> 05:49.059
MM.

05:49.059 --> 05:51.181
I'M SORRY.
YOU WERE SAYING?

05:51.181 --> 05:53.063
WAS I?

05:53.063 --> 05:55.896
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:55.896 --> 05:57.858
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

05:57.858 --> 05:59.900
[ GROANS ]

06:06.947 --> 06:08.619
GARY,
THIS IS DR. KAREV.

06:08.619 --> 06:10.040
UH, GARY WALTON, 14.

06:10.040 --> 06:11.412
COMPLAINING
OF ABDOMINAL PAIN.

06:11.412 --> 06:12.453
HOW'S IT GOING, GARY?

06:12.453 --> 06:13.834
THIS BALL LOOKS LIKE
A CHERRY.

06:13.834 --> 06:15.416
DO YOU LIKE CHERRIES?

06:15.416 --> 06:17.958
GARY WAS BORN WITH SOME
INTELLECTUAL DISABILITIES.

06:17.958 --> 06:19.710
WELL, I'M MORE OF
AN APPLE GUY MYSELF.

06:19.710 --> 06:21.051
BUT, UH,
DO YOU LIKE CHERRIES?

06:21.051 --> 06:22.463
I LOVE CHERRIES.

06:22.463 --> 06:23.554
LOVES THESE STUPID THINGS.

06:23.554 --> 06:24.595
AND THAT'S PROBABLY
WHY HE ATE ONE.

06:24.595 --> 06:26.427
JOEL!

06:26.427 --> 06:28.769
HE DID, ACTUALLY.
HE SWALLOWED THE OTHER ONE.

06:28.769 --> 06:29.890
IS HE GONNA BE OKAY?

06:29.890 --> 06:31.221
HERE IT IS ON THE X-RAY.

06:31.221 --> 06:32.973
Owen:
I CAN SHOW YOU WHERE IT IS.

06:32.973 --> 06:34.975
GARY, YOU WANT TO SHOW DR. KAREV
WHAT YOU SHOWED ME?

06:36.567 --> 06:38.439
[ GIGGLES ]

06:38.439 --> 06:39.820
[ Chuckling ] WHOA, GARY.
WHAT'D YOU DO THAT FOR?

06:39.820 --> 06:41.442
IT LOOKED LIKE A CHERRY.

06:41.442 --> 06:43.323
WELL, I BET IT DIDN'T
TASTE LIKE ONE.

06:43.323 --> 06:44.985
IT'S IN MY TUMMY NOW.
[ GIGGLES ]

06:44.985 --> 06:46.657
THIS DOCTOR SAYS
HE NEEDS SURGERY.

06:46.657 --> 06:48.078
ENDOSCOPIC SURGERY
JUST TO REMOVE THE BALL, RIGHT?

06:48.078 --> 06:49.490
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

06:49.490 --> 06:51.161
I THINK DR. SPENCER
JUMPED THE GUN A LITTLE.

06:51.161 --> 06:53.243
GARY'S BODY
HAS ITS OWN EXIT STRATEGY.

06:53.243 --> 06:54.745
GARY,
YOU'RE GONNA POOP IT.

06:54.745 --> 06:56.587
OH, HO, HO,
THAT IS GOING TO HURT.

06:56.587 --> 06:58.088
JOEL!

06:58.088 --> 07:00.000
WELL, MAYBE IT'LL KEEP HIM
FROM DOING CRAP LIKE THIS.

07:00.000 --> 07:02.543
WELL, SO DON'T WORRY.
NO SURGERY.

07:02.543 --> 07:03.964
OH, GOOD.
THANK YOU.

07:05.425 --> 07:08.048
UH...WE'LL JUST
KEEP HIM HERE OVERNIGHT,

07:08.048 --> 07:09.720
AND, UH, WE'LL MAKE SURE
EVERYTHING COMES OUT OKAY.

07:09.720 --> 07:11.011
GARY, WANT TO SLEEP OVER?

07:11.011 --> 07:12.312
YEAH!

07:12.312 --> 07:13.854
OKAY.

07:13.854 --> 07:14.895
CAN I STAY WITH HIM?

07:14.895 --> 07:16.396
UH, ABSOLUTELY.

07:16.396 --> 07:17.267
UH, YOU'RE NOT GONNA EAT THIS,
ARE YOU?

07:17.267 --> 07:20.020
NO.
ALL RIGHT.

07:20.020 --> 07:22.062
SPENCER,
I NEED YOU TO DO HOURLY CHECKS.

07:22.062 --> 07:23.694
YES, SIR.
OH, UH, JUST STEER CLEAR
OF THE MOM.

07:23.694 --> 07:25.025
SHE'S A DOC KNOCKER.

07:25.025 --> 07:26.446
A WHAT?

07:26.446 --> 07:28.989
A MOM WHO'S UP FOR MORE
THAN YOUR BEDSIDE MANNER.

07:28.989 --> 07:30.030
KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

07:31.622 --> 07:32.873
REALLY?

07:32.873 --> 07:33.994
SHE JUST SEEMS LIKE
A CONCERNED MOM TO ME.

07:33.994 --> 07:34.995
HER KID'S --

07:34.995 --> 07:36.336
JUST TRUST ME.

07:36.336 --> 07:37.788
KEEP A BUFFER
BETWEEN YOU AND HER --

07:37.788 --> 07:39.710
A STOOL, PORTABLE X-RAY --
ANYTHING.

07:39.710 --> 07:42.713
[ SCOFFS ]

07:42.713 --> 07:44.134
I HATE GUYS LIKE THAT.

07:44.134 --> 07:45.295
JUST 'CAUSE HE HAS
A HOT GIRLFRIEND,

07:45.295 --> 07:46.547
HE THINKS EVERYONE WANTS
TO BONE HIM.

07:48.348 --> 07:51.351
MR. JAFFEE,
WE'VE ALMOST GOT THE ALL-CLEAR.

07:51.351 --> 07:53.223
WE JUST NEED
TO TAKE YOU UPSTAIRS

07:53.223 --> 07:54.975
FOR A PRE-OP CHEST X-RAY
AND AN EKG,

07:54.975 --> 07:56.306
AND THEN WE'RE GOOD TO GO.

07:56.306 --> 07:58.729
SO, YOU'RE GONNA NEED
TO LOSE THE HAT.

07:58.729 --> 08:01.231
HE, UH, WON'T TAKE IT OFF.
I TRIED.

08:01.231 --> 08:03.774
LOOK, MY LATE WIFE
GAVE ME THIS HAT.

08:03.774 --> 08:07.698
YOU KNOW, I CAUGHT 22
PRIZE-WINNING BLUEGILLS IN IT!

08:07.698 --> 08:10.490
IT GOES EVERYWHERE I GO.
IT'S GOOD LUCK.

08:10.490 --> 08:12.783
AND WE FOUND YOU A KIDNEY,
SO THE HAT'S DONE ITS JOB.

08:12.783 --> 08:14.244
YEAH.

08:14.244 --> 08:15.536
WELL,
CAN'T I JUST KEEP IT?

08:15.536 --> 08:16.747
HAND IT OVER.

08:16.747 --> 08:19.289
[ SIGHS ]

08:19.289 --> 08:22.172
OKAY.
BUT, UH...

08:22.172 --> 08:24.044
OH, MY GOD.

08:24.044 --> 08:27.087
YEAH, THAT SHOWED UP
A FEW MONTHS AGO.

08:29.550 --> 08:31.221
[ MONITORS BEEPING RAPIDLY ]

08:31.221 --> 08:32.763
Nathan: CHARGE TO 100.
PRESS SYNC.

08:32.763 --> 08:33.804
CLEAR!

08:35.055 --> 08:36.767
WHAT DO WE HAVE?
HERE YOU GO.

08:36.767 --> 08:38.098
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

08:38.098 --> 08:40.440
CARDIOVERTING.
150. CLEAR!

08:40.440 --> 08:41.642
WHO ARE YOU?
GET AWAY FROM MY PATIENT!

08:41.642 --> 08:43.353
FOUND THE SCRUBS, BY THE WAY.
THANKS FOR THAT.

08:43.353 --> 08:44.945
HEY!
YOUR PATIENT?
CHARGE TO 200.

08:44.945 --> 08:46.947
HEY, I'M IN THE MIDDLE
OF DOING SOMETHING HERE!
SHE'S HYPOTENSIVE!

08:46.947 --> 08:48.699
I CAN SEE THAT!
CLEAR!

08:48.699 --> 08:50.240
Owen: RIGGS?

08:50.240 --> 08:51.612
HUNT!
DO YOU KNOW THIS PERSON?

08:51.612 --> 08:52.913
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING HERE?

08:52.913 --> 08:54.244
HEY,
I'M TRYING TO DO MY JOB!
EVERYONE STOP!

08:55.576 --> 08:57.367
WHO GAVE YOU PRIVILEGES
HERE?

08:57.367 --> 08:58.709
WELL, YOU DID.

09:00.000 --> 09:02.963
WHEN YOU HIRED ME, RIGHT?

09:02.963 --> 09:06.967
[ PADDLES WHINE ]

09:13.223 --> 09:15.475
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

09:15.475 --> 09:17.808
YOU HIRED SOMEONE FOR MY
DEPARTMENT WITHOUT TELLING ME?

09:17.808 --> 09:19.439
SHOOT.
RIGGS.

09:19.439 --> 09:22.142
UH, NO,
I WAS GOING TO TELL YOU.

09:22.142 --> 09:23.734
YOU'LL LIKE HIM.
I PROMISE.

09:23.734 --> 09:25.856
I'D LIKE TO HAVE DECIDED THAT
FOR MYSELF.

09:25.856 --> 09:27.527
OH, BUT HE'S GREAT.

09:27.527 --> 09:30.530
HE WAS IN LINE
TO BE CHIEF OF CARDIO AT DUKE.

09:30.530 --> 09:32.903
HE'S DONE INCREDIBLE AMOUNTS
OF RELIEF WORK --

09:32.903 --> 09:34.454
AND YOU HIRED HIM HERE
WITHOUT ANY DISCUSSION,

09:34.454 --> 09:35.996
WITHOUT ASKING A SINGLE --

09:35.996 --> 09:37.788
HUNT, IT'S NOT YOUR DEPARTMENT.
WHAT'S YOUR PROBLEM?

09:37.788 --> 09:41.411
LOOK, PIERCE, I'M SORRY,
BUT HE WAS AVAILABLE,

09:41.411 --> 09:43.043
WE HAD AN OPENING,
AND I MADE A CALL.

09:43.043 --> 09:44.915
AND I'M THE CHIEF.

09:44.915 --> 09:47.207
NOW, KINDLY GO AWAY.
I'M OPERATING.

09:50.380 --> 09:52.172
♪♪

09:54.925 --> 09:58.018
WELL,
THANKS FOR HAVING MY BACK.

09:58.018 --> 10:00.600
HUH? OH, RIGHT.
NO PROBLEM.

10:00.600 --> 10:02.392
SO, HOW LONG HAVE YOU HAD
THIS LUMP, SIR?

10:02.392 --> 10:04.354
OH, NOT LONG.

10:04.354 --> 10:05.986
UM...SEVEN,
EIGHT MONTHS NOW.

10:05.986 --> 10:07.818
AND YOU NEVER
HAD IT TREATED?

10:07.818 --> 10:10.070
WELL, IT WAS JUST A LITTLE BUMP
AT FIRST, YOU KNOW?

10:10.070 --> 10:11.942
I THOUGHT IT WAS A BUG BITE.

10:11.942 --> 10:14.735
AND THEN I THOUGHT
MAYBE IT WAS A CYST.

10:16.036 --> 10:17.367
AND THEN I WAS AFRAID.

10:17.367 --> 10:20.120
THAT THEY WOULD KICK YOU
OFF THE TRANSPLANT LIST.

10:20.120 --> 10:22.042
I ALREADY CALLED
THE GRANDKIDS.

10:22.042 --> 10:24.084
MAYBE I SHOULD'VE WAITED?

10:26.546 --> 10:28.458
THIS IS NOT A PLASTICS CASE.
I THINK IT'S A TUMOR.

10:28.458 --> 10:29.840
THAT'S WHAT
I WAS AFRAID OF.

10:29.840 --> 10:31.131
I MEAN,
IF THIS IS CANCER,

10:31.131 --> 10:32.753
THERE'S NO WAY
HE'S GETTING THAT KIDNEY.

10:32.753 --> 10:35.055
YEAH, IT'S LIKELY
INVADED LOCALLY, THE TUMOR.

10:35.055 --> 10:37.217
UH, IT'S POSSIBLY
METASTASIZED.
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

10:37.217 --> 10:39.259
SORRY.

10:39.259 --> 10:40.721
HEY.
DID WE GET THE PET SCANS?

10:40.721 --> 10:44.314
I THOUGHT WE WERE WAITING
ON NEURO AND ORTHO CONSULTS.

10:44.314 --> 10:45.856
OKAY, WE NEED TO RUN
ONCOLOGY STAGING

10:45.856 --> 10:47.227
ON THIS MASS RIGHT NOW.

10:47.227 --> 10:49.439
PET SCANS ASAP
WITH RENAL PRECAUTIONS.

10:49.439 --> 10:51.191
AND WHY ARE THESE CONSULTS
TAKING SO LONG?

10:51.191 --> 10:52.823
I'M SORRY.
I PUSHED.

10:52.823 --> 10:54.574
THEY WERE BUSY.
THAT'S FINE.

10:54.574 --> 10:57.447
JUST, UH, LET ME KNOW
WHEN WE GET THEM, OKAY?

10:57.447 --> 10:59.740
OKAY.

10:59.740 --> 11:01.702
WHY IS SHE GOING EASY
ON YOU?

11:01.702 --> 11:03.453
WHAT'D YOU DO?

11:03.453 --> 11:05.165
I HAVE NO IDEA.

11:05.165 --> 11:07.337
OKAY.
[ SIGHS ]

11:07.337 --> 11:08.999
HEY.
OH.

11:08.999 --> 11:10.460
UM, ANY INTEREST IN TRIVIA NIGHT
AT A LESBIAN BAR?

11:10.460 --> 11:12.713
I'M NOT SURE I KNOW THAT MUCH
ABOUT LESBIANS.

11:12.713 --> 11:14.344
FUNNY.
YOU'RE -- YOU'RE FUNNY.

11:14.344 --> 11:15.675
[ CHUCKLES WEAKLY ]
[ CHUCKLES ]

11:15.675 --> 11:17.347
UH, LISTEN, I'M JUST TRYING
TO DIP MY TOES IN THE POOL.

11:17.347 --> 11:18.348
MM.
YOU KNOW,
THE DATING POOL.

11:18.348 --> 11:19.599
IT'S BEEN A WHILE,

11:19.599 --> 11:20.761
AND I NEED, LIKE,
A WINGMAN.

11:20.761 --> 11:21.932
OR WINGWOMAN.
WHATEVER.

11:21.932 --> 11:24.264
BECAUSE WOMEN DON'T BUY
DRINKS FOR SAD LONERS --

11:24.264 --> 11:25.565
I HAVE A DATE WITH JACKSON
TONIGHT.

11:25.565 --> 11:26.686
OH, THAT'S GREAT!

11:26.686 --> 11:28.148
AAH!
I KNOW!

11:28.148 --> 11:30.360
HE, UH,
ASKED ME TO DINNER TO TALK,

11:30.360 --> 11:32.362
AND I'M TRYING REALLY HARD
NOT TO GET TOO EXCITED ABOUT IT.

11:32.362 --> 11:34.074
OH, BUT THAT'S A START,
SO...
[ SIGHS ]

11:34.074 --> 11:36.316
YES, YES,
IT'S A LIGHT

11:36.316 --> 11:37.617
AT THE END OF A LONG,
DARK TUNNEL.

11:37.617 --> 11:39.870
I'M SO GLAD, APRIL.
I'M SO --
SORRY, I --

11:39.870 --> 11:41.701
YEAH. NO.

11:41.701 --> 11:43.493
[ SIGHS ]

11:43.493 --> 11:45.535
♪♪

11:50.540 --> 11:52.252
GOT A SEC?
HEY.
WHAT'S UP?

11:52.252 --> 11:54.294
UH, WELL, UH,
LISTEN.

11:54.294 --> 11:57.798
YOU KNOW, UH,
MIRANDA AND I WERE TALKING,

11:57.798 --> 12:00.470
AND SHE --
WELL, BOTH OF US,

12:00.470 --> 12:02.933
WE WERE WONDERING
IF TONIGHT YOU MIGHT, UH --

12:02.933 --> 12:04.805
AH, I CAN'T
DO ANYTHING TONIGHT.

12:04.805 --> 12:06.977
I'M GOING TO DINNER
WITH APRIL.

12:06.977 --> 12:09.559
APRIL?
REALLY?

12:09.559 --> 12:11.021
YEAH.
I ASKED HER.

12:11.021 --> 12:12.152
YOU KNOW, I FIGURE
WE'RE IN A PRETTY GOOD PLACE,

12:12.152 --> 12:13.814
AND NOW
WE CAN ACTUALLY TALK...

12:13.814 --> 12:14.815
THAT'S FANTASTIC.

12:14.815 --> 12:16.196
...ABOUT DIVORCE.

12:16.196 --> 12:18.528
SO...
WELL, THAT'S, UM --

12:18.528 --> 12:19.619
DAMN.

12:19.619 --> 12:22.662
I'M SORRY, MAN.
I WISH THERE WAS --

12:22.662 --> 12:25.245
YEAH, I DO, TOO.
THANKS, MAN.

12:25.245 --> 12:26.326
ANOTHER NIGHT, THOUGH?

12:26.326 --> 12:28.288
ANOTHER NIGHT.

12:28.288 --> 12:30.921
ALL RIGHT.
UM, GOOD LUCK.

12:30.921 --> 12:33.834
YEAH.
SEE YOU AT HOME, BUDDY.

12:33.834 --> 12:36.376
YES, YOU WILL.

12:36.376 --> 12:39.259
I FINALLY PINNED DOWN
DR. TORRES AND DR. SHEPHERD,

12:39.259 --> 12:41.181
AND THEY'RE LOOKING
AT MR. JAFFEE'S SCANS.

12:41.181 --> 12:42.933
OKAY, GREAT.
TELL THEM I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

12:44.554 --> 12:45.555
HOW DO YOU DO THAT?

12:45.555 --> 12:47.057
HOW DO I DO WHAT?

12:47.057 --> 12:49.099
WORK WITH BLAKE AFTER...

12:49.099 --> 12:50.650
I MEAN,
HOW ARE YOU DOING THAT?

12:50.650 --> 12:53.483
[ Sighing ] OH.

12:53.483 --> 12:55.485
WELL, I THOUGHT

12:55.485 --> 12:57.657
THAT I COULD TREAT HER
LIKE ANY OTHER RESIDENT.

12:57.657 --> 12:58.989
BUT THAT WAS REALLY HARD,

12:58.989 --> 13:01.031
BECAUSE I WANTED
TO PUNCH HER IN THE FACE.

13:01.031 --> 13:02.322
LIKE, A LOT.

13:02.322 --> 13:04.534
SO NOW I'M TRYING
SOMETHING DIFFERENT.

13:04.534 --> 13:07.667
I AM KEEPING HER
ON A SHORT LEASH AT A DISTANCE

13:07.667 --> 13:09.249
SO AT LEAST SHE CAN'T
HURT ANYONE ELSE.

13:09.249 --> 13:12.502
I JUST DON'T THINK
I COULD DO THAT.

13:12.502 --> 13:14.584
WELL, SHE'S HERE.
SHE'S NOT GOING ANYWHERE, SO...

13:19.799 --> 13:21.511
[ SIGHS ]

13:21.511 --> 13:22.923
MRS. BROWN?
I'M DR. PIERCE.

13:22.923 --> 13:24.845
I'M THE CHIEF
OF CARDIOTHORACIC SURGERY.

13:24.845 --> 13:27.427
AND THIS IS DOCTOR --
DR. RIGGS.

13:27.427 --> 13:29.980
HI. WELL, I'M GLAD
TO SEE YOU AWAKE, LORETTA.

13:29.980 --> 13:31.521
YOU GAVE US A BIT OF A SCARE,
THERE.

13:31.521 --> 13:32.602
WHEN CAN I GO HOME?

13:32.602 --> 13:34.354
UH, I'D LIKE TO RUN
SOME MORE TESTS

13:34.354 --> 13:36.486
TO DETERMINE
WHETHER YOU'LL NEED SURGERY.

13:36.486 --> 13:38.028
WE'VE CALLED YOUR FAMILY.
THEY'RE ON THEIR WAY.

13:38.028 --> 13:41.701
DR. RIGGS,
DO YOU THINK I NEED SURGERY?

13:41.701 --> 13:44.034
WELL, YOUR ECHO SHOWS
A REDUCTION IN BLOOD FLOW

13:44.034 --> 13:45.245
THROUGH ONE OF THE VALVES
IN YOUR HEART,

13:45.245 --> 13:47.117
SO WE JUST WANT
TO MAKE SURE THAT --

13:47.117 --> 13:49.829
I'D LIKE TO KEEP YOU OVERNIGHT
TO RUN SOME MORE TESTS.

13:49.829 --> 13:51.661
AND I'LL TAKE IT FROM THERE,
OKAY?

13:51.661 --> 13:53.453
DR. RIGGS?

13:53.453 --> 13:55.625
YOU'RE GONNA BE
WELL TAKEN CARE OF.

14:01.801 --> 14:03.463
IT'S YOUR FIRST DAY.

14:03.463 --> 14:06.056
MIGHT WANT TO GET YOUR FEET WET
BEFORE YOU DIVE IN.

14:06.056 --> 14:08.178
MM.

14:08.178 --> 14:10.020
MY FEET WERE PRETTY WET
WHEN I GOT HERE.

14:10.020 --> 14:13.353
THEN YOU CAN GET ME
A CARDIAC-GATED CT

14:13.353 --> 14:15.815
AND DO
A RISK STRATIFICATION.

14:15.815 --> 14:17.067
PAGE ME WITH THE RESULTS.

14:17.067 --> 14:19.689
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

14:19.689 --> 14:20.530
YES, MA'AM.

14:20.530 --> 14:21.942
THANK YOU.

14:26.536 --> 14:28.868
[ COMPUTER BEEPING ]

14:28.868 --> 14:30.250
WELL?

14:30.250 --> 14:32.542
OSTEOSARCOMA.

14:32.542 --> 14:33.994
IT INVOLVES THE FRONTAL
AND THE OCCIPITAL BONE.

14:33.994 --> 14:35.415
IT'S LOCALLY
VERY AGGRESSIVE.

14:35.415 --> 14:36.917
IT'S A LOVELY TUMOR.

14:36.917 --> 14:39.629
IT'S ALMOST CUTE.
JUST PLOPPED THERE.

14:39.629 --> 14:40.710
"HELLO."

14:40.710 --> 14:42.502
HE'S WAITED 18 MONTHS
FOR THIS KIDNEY.

14:42.502 --> 14:44.594
WE FINALLY HAVE ONE,
AND NOW HE HAS CANCER?

14:44.594 --> 14:45.966
WHAT IF HE DIDN'T?

14:45.966 --> 14:46.967
DIDN'T WHAT?

14:46.967 --> 14:48.268
HAVE CANCER.

14:48.268 --> 14:49.309
HIS TUMOR
HAS GORGEOUS MARGINS.

14:49.309 --> 14:52.272
IT'S LIKE A RIPE,
JUICY PIECE OF FRUIT

14:52.272 --> 14:53.773
THAT'S HUNG LOW
ON THE BRANCH.

14:53.773 --> 14:55.065
I COULD REACH IN
AND PLUCK IT.

14:57.187 --> 14:59.069
[ Muffled ]
NO CANCER, NO PROBLEM.

14:59.069 --> 15:00.941
YOU CAN DO THAT?
NO.

15:00.941 --> 15:02.232
EVEN IF YOU CAN
REMOVE IT --

15:02.232 --> 15:03.984
[ Normal voice ]
OH, I CAN.

15:03.984 --> 15:05.905
WELL, HE'S LEFT WITH
A GAPING HOLE IN HIS HEAD.

15:05.905 --> 15:07.077
NO SKULL,
NO SKIN TO COVER IT.

15:07.077 --> 15:08.698
I FIX BRAINS.

15:08.698 --> 15:09.789
[ SIGHS ]
I GIVE YOU YOUR SOFT,
GOOEY CENTER.

15:09.789 --> 15:11.491
THE HARD CANDY SHELL
IS YOUR DEPARTMENT.

15:11.491 --> 15:12.832
NO, THERE'S NO WAY
TO CLOSE IT.

15:12.832 --> 15:14.294
NOT EVEN A ROTATIONAL FLAP.

15:14.294 --> 15:16.086
THERE'S NOTHING
TO WORK WITH HERE.

15:16.086 --> 15:18.088
AND A WOUND THAT SIZE,

15:18.088 --> 15:20.040
WHEN HIS IMMUNE SYSTEM
IS ALREADY COMPROMISED,

15:20.040 --> 15:21.671
THAT COULD KICK HIM
OFF THE TRANSPLANT LIST.

15:21.671 --> 15:25.255
[ SIGHS ]

15:25.255 --> 15:27.467
WE HAVE LESS THAN 24 HOURS
BEFORE WE LOSE THE KIDNEY.

15:27.467 --> 15:30.850
SO, WILSON AND EDWARDS,
I NEED IDEAS.

15:30.850 --> 15:32.512
CRAZY IDEAS, SMART IDEAS.

15:32.512 --> 15:34.814
GIVE ME ANYTHING THAT WILL
CLOSE MR. JAFFEE'S HEAD

15:34.814 --> 15:36.316
SO HE CAN SURVIVE THIS SURGERY.

15:36.316 --> 15:37.607
GO. HIT THE BOOKS.
FIND ME SOMETHING.

15:37.607 --> 15:38.728
ON IT.
ABSOLUTELY.

15:38.728 --> 15:40.650
♪♪

15:40.650 --> 15:42.022
DR. GREY?

15:42.022 --> 15:44.774
SHOULD I LOOK TOO, OR...?

15:44.774 --> 15:47.237
BLAKE.
NO, YOU SHOULD, UM...

15:47.237 --> 15:50.160
GO MONITOR THE DONOR.
DO THAT.

15:52.622 --> 15:55.665
MAKE SURE THE BRAIN-DEAD GUY
IS STILL BRAIN-DEAD.

15:55.665 --> 15:57.787
RIGHT.

16:03.343 --> 16:05.085
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

16:05.085 --> 16:06.216
EXCUSE ME?

16:06.216 --> 16:07.887
"MONITOR THE DONOR"?

16:07.887 --> 16:10.390
YOU'VE GOT BLAKE DOING SCUT
THAT AN INTERN COULD DO.

16:10.390 --> 16:12.762
SHE IS HERE TO LEARN.
AND, WELL, I --

16:12.762 --> 16:14.434
LISTEN, CALLIE.

16:14.434 --> 16:17.937
WHEN I TEACH HER,
YOU SAY I AM BEATING HER DOWN.

16:17.937 --> 16:20.020
WHEN I'M NICE TO HER,
YOU SAY I'M NEGLECTING HER.

16:20.020 --> 16:21.311
NO, NO, NO.

16:21.311 --> 16:22.602
YOU'RE NEGLECTING
YOUR RESPONSIBILITY.

16:22.602 --> 16:24.364
AND IF SHE WERE
ANY OTHER RESIDENT --

16:24.364 --> 16:25.695
IF SHE WERE
ANY OTHER RESIDENT,

16:25.695 --> 16:27.567
YOU WOULDN'T BE TALKING TO ME
RIGHT NOW, CALLIE.

16:27.567 --> 16:29.489
[ SCOFFS ]
I'M DONE TALKING
ABOUT YOUR GIRLFRIEND.

16:29.489 --> 16:31.111
THIS IS YOUR PROBLEM.

16:31.111 --> 16:33.073
IT'S NOT BLAKE'S,
AND IT'S NOT MINE.

16:34.574 --> 16:36.576
THAT'S...

16:37.917 --> 16:38.918
[ SCOFFS ]

16:46.676 --> 16:48.468
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

16:50.630 --> 16:52.222
AAH. [ CHUCKLES ]
OH.

16:52.222 --> 16:54.394
OH, I DIDN'T MEAN
TO STARTLE YOU.

16:54.394 --> 16:56.226
IS HE OKAY?

16:56.226 --> 16:58.188
YE-- LISTEN, YOU HAVE NOTHING
TO WORRY ABOUT.

16:58.188 --> 16:59.269
GARY'S GONNA BE FINE.

16:59.269 --> 17:00.980
I IMAGINE
IT'S NOT THE FIRST TIME

17:00.980 --> 17:02.062
HE'S DONE SOMETHING
LIKE THIS.

17:02.062 --> 17:03.193
YOU'RE RIGHT.
YOU GET IT.

17:03.193 --> 17:05.695
YOU KNOW, IT CAN
JUST BE SO HARD SOMETIMES.

17:05.695 --> 17:10.820
YOU KNOW, HE'S A GREAT KID,
BUT [SIGHS] HE CAN BE A LOT.

17:10.820 --> 17:13.243
WELL,
YOU'RE DOING A GREAT JOB.

17:13.243 --> 17:15.245
HE'S A GREAT KID.
[ CHUCKLES ] THANK YOU.

17:15.245 --> 17:16.576
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

17:16.576 --> 17:18.658
YOU KNOW, YOU'RE --
YOU'RE SO NICE, AND SO HELPFUL.

17:18.658 --> 17:19.659
THANK YOU.

17:19.659 --> 17:20.790
OH, UH, THAT'S --

17:20.790 --> 17:22.082
IT'S NOT A PROBLEM
AT ALL.

17:22.082 --> 17:23.963
OH. UM...

17:23.963 --> 17:26.256
UH-OH. MNH.
UM, MA'AM...

17:26.256 --> 17:28.428
MA'AM!
IT'S ELAINE.

17:28.428 --> 17:29.669
OH, UH, ELAINE, MA'AM, I...

17:29.669 --> 17:31.471
I-I -- 'CAUSE I HAVE
THE OTHER PATIENTS.

17:31.471 --> 17:33.473
BUT I'LL -- I'LL --
UH, BYE.

17:33.473 --> 17:34.594
YEAH, BYE.

17:34.594 --> 17:35.515
I'LL SEE YOU IN AN HOUR?!

17:37.137 --> 17:38.938
FINALLY.
GOD, WHAT TOOK SO LONG?

17:38.938 --> 17:41.020
WHOA, RELAX.
THIS WAS NICE OF ME, REMEMBER?

17:41.020 --> 17:42.852
I DIDN'T KNOW
YOU WERE GONNA MAKE THE FOOD.

17:42.852 --> 17:44.274
SHE'S CRANKY.

17:44.274 --> 17:46.946
BAILEY HIRED A NEW CARDIO GUY
WITHOUT TELLING HER.

17:46.946 --> 17:48.648
THAT'S JACKED.
WHO IS THIS GUY?

17:48.648 --> 17:50.650
IT JUST MEANS I'M GONNA
HAVE TO TRAIN ANOTHER ALPHA MALE

17:50.650 --> 17:52.031
NOT TO PEE
ALL OVER THE PLACE.

17:52.031 --> 17:53.533
MNH.
I HATE IT WHEN THEY PEE.

17:53.533 --> 17:55.034
DEREK PEED A LOT.

17:55.034 --> 17:56.075
OH, COME ON.
WE'RE NOT LIKE THAT.

17:56.075 --> 17:57.657
WHEN YOU GOT HERE,
YOU PEED EVERYWHERE.

17:57.657 --> 17:58.828
IT WAS DISGUSTING.

17:58.828 --> 18:00.460
YOU HAD TO BE TRAINED.
NOBODY TRAINED ME.

18:00.460 --> 18:01.911
WE TRAINED YOU.
IT WAS SUBTLE.

18:01.911 --> 18:04.043
YOU DIDN'T NOTICE.

18:04.043 --> 18:05.255
IS THAT WHY
YOU MADE ME GET THE FOOD?

18:05.255 --> 18:07.207
NOT EVEN THAT.
IT'S THE PATIENTS.

18:07.207 --> 18:08.918
IT'S THE WAY
THAT THEY ALWAYS LOOK

18:08.918 --> 18:10.170
TO THE MAN IN THE ROOM FIRST

18:10.170 --> 18:11.591
NO MATTER
WHO IS TALKING TO THEM.

18:11.591 --> 18:12.472
YES.

18:12.472 --> 18:14.514
THAT'S A THING?
NOT FOR YOU.

18:14.514 --> 18:17.267
AND THEN THERE'S
THE WHOLE OTHER THING.

18:17.267 --> 18:18.768
[ SCOFFS ]

18:18.768 --> 18:21.311
YOU KNOW, I JUST -- I THOUGHT
I WAS DONE WITH THAT HERE.

18:21.311 --> 18:23.603
THIS GUY JUST COMES IN.

18:23.603 --> 18:24.894
HE'S TAKING CONSULTS WITHOUT
EVEN TALKING TO ME ABOUT IT --

18:24.894 --> 18:26.986
WHAT WHOLE OTHER THING?

18:28.027 --> 18:31.070
THAT?

18:31.070 --> 18:32.902
COME ON,
IS THAT A THING?

18:32.902 --> 18:34.284
OF COURSE IT IS.

18:34.284 --> 18:35.285
HERE?

18:35.285 --> 18:37.497
YEAH, HERE.
ANYWHERE.

18:37.497 --> 18:38.828
ASK EDWARDS.
ASK BAILEY.

18:38.828 --> 18:41.120
I CAN'T BELIEVE THAT.

18:41.120 --> 18:43.293
THAT'S 'CAUSE
IT'S NOT YOUR THING.

18:43.293 --> 18:45.455
♪♪

18:45.455 --> 18:47.417
[ GIGGLES ]

18:47.417 --> 18:48.878
OKAY,
TELL ME WHAT YOU SAID TO HIM.

18:48.878 --> 18:51.461
HOW DID YOU FIGHT
FOR OUR LOVE?

18:53.092 --> 18:55.595
♪ LIKE SEVEN INCHES
FROM THE MIDDAY SUN ♪
WELL, UM...

18:55.595 --> 18:57.427
WHAT?
I, UH...

18:57.427 --> 18:59.929
♪ I HEAR YOU WHISPER ♪
WHAT DID YOU SAY?

18:59.929 --> 19:01.971
♪ AND THE WORDS
MELT EVERYONE ♪

19:01.971 --> 19:04.684
WELL, I STARTED TO, AND --

19:04.684 --> 19:07.146
LOOK, I WOULD HAVE,
BUT HE -- HE -- HE TOLD ME

19:07.146 --> 19:08.818
HE'S TALKING TO APRIL
ABOUT DIVORCE,

19:08.818 --> 19:10.610
AND SO --
HE'S COMING BACK HERE?

19:10.610 --> 19:13.533
DO YOU GET HOW SERIOUS
THIS IS?

19:13.533 --> 19:16.236
OH, I AM OFF MY GAME.

19:16.236 --> 19:17.537
UGH.

19:17.537 --> 19:19.239
I HIRED A NEW CARDIO SURGEON
AND FORGOT TO TELL PIERCE.

19:19.239 --> 19:21.160
THAT'S ALL THE MORE REASON
FOR US TO USE THIS TIME

19:21.160 --> 19:22.542
RIGHT NOW
WHILE WE HAVE IT.

19:22.542 --> 19:23.873
WHEN -- WHEN HE'S OUT

19:23.873 --> 19:25.785
AT WHAT IS BOUND TO BE
A VERY, VERY LONG DINNER.

19:25.785 --> 19:26.996
OH, NO, NO.

19:26.996 --> 19:28.628
HE COULD COME BACK HERE
ANY MINUTE

19:28.628 --> 19:29.959
IN THE MIDDLE OF STUFF!

19:29.959 --> 19:31.381
OKAY, THIS IS OUR WINDOW,
MIRANDA.

19:31.381 --> 19:32.712
HE'S ASKING FOR A DIVORCE.

19:32.712 --> 19:34.254
THERE'S NO TELLING WHEN
WE'RE GETTING OUR SOFA BACK!

19:34.254 --> 19:35.295
OH, YES, THERE IS.

19:35.295 --> 19:37.677
IT'S WHEN YOU TELL HIM
TO GET THE HELL OUT!

19:37.677 --> 19:39.349
WHEN YOU GET HIM TO SAY, UH,
"THANK YOU FOR YOUR HOSPITALITY.

19:39.349 --> 19:42.011
IT IS TIME FOR ME TO LEAVE
YOUR SOFA."

19:42.011 --> 19:44.143
MIRANDA, COME --
NO!

19:44.143 --> 19:46.185
YOU DON'T GET IT
UNTIL YOU GET IT.

19:46.185 --> 19:49.569
♪ AND IT'S JUST LIKE THE OCEAN
UNDER THE MOON ♪

19:49.569 --> 19:51.811
♪ IT'S THE SAME AS THE EMOTION
THAT I GET FROM YOU ♪
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

19:51.811 --> 19:54.734
OH,
THAT WAS DELICIOUS.

19:54.734 --> 19:56.946
YEAH, THEIR PUMPKIN RAVIOLI
NEVER DISAPPOINTS.

19:56.946 --> 19:59.078
THIS HAS BEEN REALLY NICE.

19:59.078 --> 20:00.079
YEAH.

20:01.411 --> 20:04.163
WE SOMEHOW MANAGED
TO FINISH OUR MEAL

20:04.163 --> 20:05.164
WITHOUT ACTUALLY...

20:05.164 --> 20:07.827
TALKING. RIGHT.
...TALKING.

20:07.827 --> 20:10.630
DO WE NEED TO, THOUGH?

20:10.630 --> 20:12.131
I-I WANT TO.

20:12.131 --> 20:13.793
IF YOU DO.

20:13.793 --> 20:16.386
BUT IT...

20:16.386 --> 20:19.969
IT'S BEEN SO NICE
JUST HAVING A MEAL WITH YOU.

20:19.969 --> 20:23.263
WE REALLY SHOULD, THOUGH.

20:23.263 --> 20:24.724
WE SHOULD TALK.

20:24.724 --> 20:29.609
YES. YES.
WE SHOULD.

20:29.609 --> 20:32.061
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

20:32.061 --> 20:33.273
DAMN IT.

20:34.984 --> 20:37.116
I'M --
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

20:37.116 --> 20:38.988
DUTY CALLS.
IT'S FINE.

20:38.988 --> 20:41.701
I WANT TO KEEP TALKING,
THOUGH.

20:41.701 --> 20:43.032
I DO.

20:43.032 --> 20:45.455
UM...

20:45.455 --> 20:46.536
TOMORROW NIGHT?

20:46.536 --> 20:48.578
TOMORROW NIGHT.

20:48.578 --> 20:49.789
OKAY.

20:49.789 --> 20:51.921
♪ MY WORLD
TO LIFT YOU UP ♪

20:51.921 --> 20:58.928
♪ I WOULD CHANGE MY LIFE
TO BETTER SUIT YOUR MOOD ♪

20:58.928 --> 21:01.641
Owen: HELP. HELP!

21:01.641 --> 21:04.474
♪ BECAUSE YOU'RE SO SMOOTH ♪

21:05.435 --> 21:07.687
SOMEONE, PLEASE.

21:07.687 --> 21:09.809
DO SOMETHING.
DR. HUNT?

21:09.809 --> 21:11.851
I CAN'T FIND HER.

21:11.851 --> 21:13.563
I-I -- FIND WHO?

21:13.563 --> 21:16.396
DR. HUNT.

21:16.396 --> 21:18.698
NO, DO SOMETHING!
DR. HUNT.
DR. HUNT, DR. HUNT.

21:21.661 --> 21:22.782
ARE YOU OKAY?

21:22.782 --> 21:24.404
I'M SORRY.
SORRY.

21:24.404 --> 21:25.995
I WAS JUST SLEEPING.
SORRY. YOU CAN GO.

21:25.995 --> 21:27.497
[ SNIFFLES ]

21:29.369 --> 21:30.540
ARE YOU SURE THAT --
GET OUT.

21:33.002 --> 21:37.126
♪ OH, FORGET ABOUT IT ♪

21:43.092 --> 21:45.094
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

21:45.094 --> 21:47.306
HERE?

21:47.306 --> 21:49.979
DR. GREY SAID MONITOR.
I AM MONITORING.

21:49.979 --> 21:52.231
[ SIGHS ]
ANY LUCK?

21:52.231 --> 21:54.564
WITH THE HOLE
IN MR. JAFFEE'S HEAD?

21:54.564 --> 21:55.735
NOPE.

21:55.735 --> 21:57.647
3-D PRINTING
WILL TAKE TOO LONG.

21:57.647 --> 22:01.781
A CUSTOM-BASED CRANIOPLASTY
WON'T WORK, SO I'M...

22:01.781 --> 22:03.863
HOW'S THE HOLY GRAIL?

22:03.863 --> 22:06.536
CAN WE NOT CALL HIM THAT?

22:06.536 --> 22:08.368
SORRY. JUST...

22:08.368 --> 22:10.500
HE WAS SOMEONE'S FAMILY MEMBER,
YOU KNOW?

22:10.500 --> 22:13.913
SOMEONE'S HUSBAND,
SOMEONE'S DAD.

22:15.715 --> 22:18.668
TO SOMEONE,
HE WAS EVERYTHING.

22:21.220 --> 22:24.384
AND NOW HE'S EVERYTHING
TO MR. JAFFEE.

22:24.384 --> 22:26.676
BUT AFTER ALL THIS TIME
AND WAITING,

22:26.676 --> 22:31.310
WE PROBABLY WON'T EVEN
GET TO USE HIM.

22:31.310 --> 22:34.564
HE'S EVERYTHING,
AND IT DOESN'T EVEN MATTER.

22:34.564 --> 22:35.935
IT MEANS NOTHING.

22:35.935 --> 22:37.977
I KNOW.

22:37.977 --> 22:39.819
IT DOESN'T SEEM FAIR.

22:39.819 --> 22:41.861
♪♪

22:43.653 --> 22:44.984
HE'S EVERYTHING.

22:44.984 --> 22:47.196
PARDON?

22:47.196 --> 22:50.490
HE'S EVERYTHING.
OH, MY GOD, HE'S EVERYTHING!

22:54.874 --> 22:56.756
A SKULL TRANSPLANT?

22:56.756 --> 22:59.378
SKULL AND SCALP,
ACTUALLY.

22:59.378 --> 23:02.712
OUR KIDNEY DONOR IS A PERFECT
MATCH FOR MR. JAFFEE,

23:02.712 --> 23:05.765
WHICH MEANS THAT HE'S ALSO
A MATCH FOR THE SKULL AND SCALP.

23:05.765 --> 23:07.427
LOWER RISK OF REJECTION.

23:07.427 --> 23:09.308
HE'S EVERYTHING.

23:09.308 --> 23:10.349
WE'LL HAVE
ALL THE VASCULARIZED BONE

23:10.349 --> 23:11.641
AND SKIN THAT WE NEED
FROM THE DONOR.

23:11.641 --> 23:12.602
HAVE YOU DONE THIS BEFORE?

23:12.602 --> 23:14.393
I HAVEN'T.

23:14.393 --> 23:16.566
IT'S BEEN DONE ONCE.

23:16.566 --> 23:18.898
IT'S A COMPLEX SURGERY,
BUT I THINK IT'LL WORK.

23:18.898 --> 23:20.279
SAME DONOR, SAME SURGERY.

23:20.279 --> 23:22.021
WELL,
I'LL START ON THE TUMOR

23:22.021 --> 23:23.823
WHILE YOU TWO START
ORGAN RECOVERY.

23:23.823 --> 23:25.154
LET'S GO GET OUR KIDNEY.

23:32.291 --> 23:34.874
HEY. UM, COME OUT FOR A DRINK
WITH ME TONIGHT?

23:34.874 --> 23:36.956
IT'LL BE FUN.
IT'S TRIVIA NIGHT.

23:36.956 --> 23:38.167
IT CAN EITHER BE FUN
OR IT CAN BE TRIVIA NIGHT.

23:38.167 --> 23:39.418
COME ON.
BROADEN YOUR HORIZONS.

23:39.418 --> 23:40.750
PLUS, I DON'T REALLY WANT
TO GO ALONE...

23:40.750 --> 23:41.801
UH, ROBBINS.
HUH?

23:43.042 --> 23:45.545
DID YOU KNOW
THAT HENRI GIFFARD

23:45.545 --> 23:48.598
BUILT THE FIRST
POWERED AIRSHIP IN 1852?

23:48.598 --> 23:50.349
♪♪

23:50.349 --> 23:51.761
UM...

23:53.603 --> 23:55.144
UH, NO.

23:55.144 --> 23:57.897
I DID.

23:57.897 --> 23:59.148
AND I'M FREE TONIGHT.

23:59.148 --> 24:00.189
[ GASPS ]

24:00.189 --> 24:02.522
I'M ALWAYS FREE
FOR TRIVIA NIGHT.

24:02.522 --> 24:05.114
HMM.

24:05.114 --> 24:06.736
[ MONITORS BEEPING RAPIDLY ]

24:06.736 --> 24:07.697
RIGGS, WHAT HAPPENED?

24:07.697 --> 24:09.158
HER HEART'S FAILING.

24:09.158 --> 24:11.741
I'VE ASKED FOR A BALLOON PUMP
TO BUY US SOME TIME.

24:11.741 --> 24:14.243
WHAT SHE NEEDS
IS A VALVE REPLACEMENT, STAT.
EVEN BETTER.

24:14.243 --> 24:15.745
CALL UP FOR AN O.R.
LET'S PREP HER FOR A STERNOTOMY.

24:15.745 --> 24:17.126
KRISTA,
NOT A STERNOTOMY.

24:17.126 --> 24:19.128
KEEP PREPPING
FOR A CATH PROCEDURE.
NO.

24:19.128 --> 24:21.380
NO?
NO.
I NEED TO OPEN HER UP.

24:21.380 --> 24:22.542
SHE WON'T SURVIVE
BEING OPEN THAT LONG.

24:22.542 --> 24:24.794
I'LL NEVER GET A CATHETER
ALL THE WAY UP INTO THE HEART.

24:24.794 --> 24:26.295
RIGGS,
I AM DOING THIS PROCEDURE.

24:26.295 --> 24:28.467
AND YOU WILL BE DOING
THE WRONG PROCEDURE.

24:28.467 --> 24:30.259
PREP FOR A TAVR.
Woman: RIGHT AWAY, DOCTOR.

24:30.259 --> 24:31.681
MY NAME IS ON HER CHART.

24:31.681 --> 24:34.353
I WANT TO BE IN THAT ROOM SO
THAT IF SOMETHING GOES WRONG --

24:34.353 --> 24:37.146
DON'T WORRY, RIGGS.
IF SHE DIES, IT'LL BE MY FAULT.

24:37.146 --> 24:39.058
Man: MY WIFE'S DYING?

24:48.277 --> 24:51.661
UH, MR. BROWN.
HELLO.

24:51.661 --> 24:53.452
WE'RE TAKING LORETTA
UP TO SURGERY RIGHT NOW.
OKAY.

24:53.452 --> 24:55.494
WE'RE GOING TO DO
EVERYTHING WE CAN.

24:55.494 --> 24:57.577
[ CRYING, YELLING ]

24:57.577 --> 24:59.418
HANG IN THERE, GARY.

24:59.418 --> 25:01.330
HOW LONG AGO
DID THE LIGHT STOP BLINKING?

25:01.330 --> 25:02.752
IT STOPPED?
I-I-I'M NOT SURE.

25:02.752 --> 25:05.545
I MIGHT'VE MISSED
THE LAST COUPLE CHECKS.

25:05.545 --> 25:06.716
TELL ME WHAT'S WRONG HERE.

25:06.716 --> 25:09.719
THE BALL CAME APART?

25:09.719 --> 25:11.631
THE BALL CAME APART.

25:11.631 --> 25:13.763
AND THE BALL HAD
LITTLE BLINKING LIGHTS.

25:13.763 --> 25:15.555
SO WHAT IS MISSING?

25:15.555 --> 25:17.136
I-I DON'T, UH...

25:17.136 --> 25:18.558
[ SIGHS ]

25:18.558 --> 25:20.560
A BATTERY.
RIGHT.

25:20.560 --> 25:23.983
NOW THE BATTERY
IS ALL THE WAY OVER HERE.

25:23.983 --> 25:25.064
NOW, IF THE ACID
FROM THE BATTERY

25:25.064 --> 25:25.775
EATS THROUGH
HIS INTESTINE...

25:25.775 --> 25:28.527
IT'LL PERF HIS BOWEL.

25:28.527 --> 25:30.149
WELL, COULD WE GET IT
WITH AN ENDOSCOPE?

25:30.149 --> 25:32.361
WELL, WE COULD HAVE.
BUT NOW, THANKS TO YOU,
I HAVE TO OPEN HIM UP.

25:32.361 --> 25:34.824
SO NOTIFY KAREV
THAT I'M TAKING GARY TO SURGERY,

25:34.824 --> 25:37.116
THEN YOU GET A FRONT-ROW SEAT
TO HOW BAD YOU SCREWED THIS UP.

25:40.079 --> 25:41.540
ALL RIGHT.
SEE YOU IN THERE.

25:41.540 --> 25:43.002
YOU WON'T, ACTUALLY.

25:43.002 --> 25:44.714
I'LL BE IN THE DONOR'S O.R.

25:44.714 --> 25:46.966
MAKING SURE THAT THE KIDNEY
DOESN'T GROW LEGS AND WALK AWAY.

25:46.966 --> 25:48.668
WHAT?

25:48.668 --> 25:51.090
GREY HAS ME BABYSITTING
THE KIDNEY UNTIL SHE NEEDS IT.

25:51.090 --> 25:52.672
OH, COME ON!
CALLIE.

25:52.672 --> 25:54.133
THAT IS --

25:55.725 --> 25:57.386
GREY.
YEAH?

25:57.386 --> 25:59.228
BLAKE
IS A THIRD-YEAR RESIDENT.

25:59.228 --> 26:02.271
SHE SHOULD BE IN OUR SURGERY.
THE SKULL TRANSPLANT.

26:02.271 --> 26:03.983
THAT IS
THE LEARNING OPPORTUNITY HERE.

26:03.983 --> 26:05.144
[ SIGHS ]
SHE DESERVES
A CHANCE TO SEE IT.

26:05.144 --> 26:07.236
CALLIE...

26:07.236 --> 26:08.277
CALLIE,
WE TALKED ABOUT THIS.

26:08.277 --> 26:11.110
BLAKE NEEDS TO BE
WHERE I NEED HER TO BE.

26:11.110 --> 26:12.612
YOU DON'T NEED HER
WITH THE DONOR.

26:12.612 --> 26:14.193
YOU JUST WANT HER THERE.
WHAT FOR? WHY?

26:14.193 --> 26:15.494
WHY ARE YOU DOING THIS?
WHAT --

26:15.494 --> 26:16.696
WHAT, DO YOU JUST WANT HER
TO SIT THERE

26:16.696 --> 26:18.748
AND THINK ABOUT
WHAT HAPPENED TO DEREK?

26:18.748 --> 26:19.869
CALLIE, STOP.
NO, I AM SORRY, BUT I CAN'T
JUST STAND HERE AND --

26:19.869 --> 26:21.160
YOU'RE EMBARRASSING ME!

26:21.160 --> 26:23.002
NOBODY ASKED YOU
TO SAY ANYTHING,

26:23.002 --> 26:25.254
SO JUST SHUT UP
AND STAY OUT OF IT.

26:25.254 --> 26:27.046
♪♪

26:33.212 --> 26:36.265
ALL RIGHT.

26:36.265 --> 26:39.138
NOW, I NEED YOU TO --
HOLD ON.

26:39.138 --> 26:40.810
I DON'T NEED HER
TO FIGHT FOR ME,

26:40.810 --> 26:42.391
BUT --
BUT CALLIE IS RIGHT.

26:42.391 --> 26:43.683
I'M HERE TO LEARN.

26:43.683 --> 26:46.435
I WANT TO LEARN,
BUT YOU HAVE TO TEACH ME.

26:46.435 --> 26:48.688
DON'T GO EASY ON ME.
DON'T EXPECT LESS.

26:48.688 --> 26:50.319
TREAT ME LIKE
ANY OTHER RESIDENT.

26:50.319 --> 26:52.571
TREAT ME WORSE.
I DON'T CARE.

26:52.571 --> 26:54.864
HATE ME, YELL AT ME,
I CAN HANDLE IT.

26:54.864 --> 26:56.035
I WILL HANDLE IT.

26:56.035 --> 26:58.117
YOU TOLD ME NOT TO QUIT,
AND I DIDN'T.

26:58.117 --> 26:59.498
BUT YOU ARE RIGHT NOW.

26:59.498 --> 27:02.912
AND IF YOU CAN'T DO
WHAT YOU ARE HERE TO DO,

27:02.912 --> 27:06.335
THEN PLEASE LET ME GO.

27:06.335 --> 27:08.087
♪♪

27:13.422 --> 27:16.345
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

27:16.345 --> 27:17.717
ARE YOU GONNA DO SOMETHING?

27:17.717 --> 27:19.468
I'M THINKING.

27:23.392 --> 27:25.224
LET'S PREP FOR A STERNOTOMY.
LET'S OPEN HER UP.

27:25.224 --> 27:26.645
GOOD CHOICE.
I KNOW.

27:26.645 --> 27:28.477
OH, COME ON.
YOU CAN SAY I WAS RIGHT.

27:28.477 --> 27:31.190
YOU WEREN'T. SHE WON'T SURVIVE
A SIX-HOUR PROCEDURE.

27:31.190 --> 27:34.113
IT'S HER BEST SHOT.
LISTEN, I GET IT, OKAY?

27:34.113 --> 27:35.735
I'D HATE ME, TOO,
THE WAY I WAS HIRED.

27:35.735 --> 27:36.655
BAILEY SHOULD'VE TOLD YOU.

27:36.655 --> 27:37.987
10 BLADE.

27:37.987 --> 27:40.119
BAILEY IS THE CHIEF.

27:40.119 --> 27:41.741
YEAH,
BUT IT WAS PRETTY MESSED UP.

27:41.741 --> 27:42.992
I MEAN, YOU AND I SHOULD'VE HAD
A PROPER SIT-DOWN.

27:42.992 --> 27:45.084
I AGREE.
SAW, PLEASE.

27:45.084 --> 27:46.625
YOU'D HAVE SEEN ME
IN MY SUIT.

27:46.625 --> 27:47.957
IT'S NICE.

27:47.957 --> 27:51.090
I MEAN, IT'S PROBABLY WRINKLED,
BUT IT'S CLEAN.

27:51.090 --> 27:52.752
NO, IT'S DEFINITELY,
DEFINITELY CLEAN.

27:52.752 --> 27:54.093
YOU WOULD'VE ASKED ME
WHERE I'M FROM.

27:54.093 --> 27:56.215
AUSTRALIA.
RETRACT.

27:56.215 --> 27:58.097
AND YOU'D GUESS WRONG.
NEW ZEALAND.

27:58.097 --> 28:00.219
A COMMON MISTAKE.

28:00.219 --> 28:02.722
SEATTLE WHEN I WAS 7,
THEN MED SCHOOL, FELLOWSHIP.

28:02.722 --> 28:04.013
THE MIDDLE EAST FOR A LONG TIME.

28:04.013 --> 28:06.475
PREPARE TO MAKE
A LARGE AORTIC PURSE STRING.

28:06.475 --> 28:07.727
WHY?

28:07.727 --> 28:09.568
JUST DO IT.

28:09.568 --> 28:11.941
WHY THE MIDDLE EAST?

28:11.941 --> 28:13.402
OH, RELIEF WORK.

28:13.402 --> 28:16.525
I LIKE THE PACE, THE PEOPLE,
IMPROVISATION.

28:16.525 --> 28:19.739
I ONCE RE-INFLATED
A COLLAPSED PULMONARY ARTERY

28:19.739 --> 28:22.661
ON A DIRT ROAD WITH A STRAW
AND A SET OF CAR KEYS.

28:22.661 --> 28:24.283
OH, YOU'D LIKE THAT STORY.

28:24.283 --> 28:26.665
OOH, YEAH,
YOU'D BE ASKING ME ALL ABOUT IT.

28:26.665 --> 28:27.917
YOU'D BE SO IMPRESSED.

28:27.917 --> 28:30.249
YOU'D BE THINKING,
"WOW! HE'S SO INNOVATIVE.

28:30.249 --> 28:31.460
AND HE'S QUICK.
I SHOULD HIRE HIM."

28:31.460 --> 28:32.591
WOULD I?
MM-HMM.

28:32.591 --> 28:33.883
HMM.
OH, YES.

28:33.883 --> 28:35.384
AT THIS POINT,
THE INTERVIEW'S GOING VERY WELL.

28:35.384 --> 28:36.675
TAKE THIS.

28:36.675 --> 28:37.967
3-0 PROLENE.

28:37.967 --> 28:41.470
BUT THE KICKER
IS WHEN I ASK ABOUT YOU.

28:41.470 --> 28:43.893
HOW YOU LANDED A FELLOWSHIP
AT THE AGE OF 25.

28:43.893 --> 28:45.644
HOW YOU MADE CHIEF OF CARDIO
AT AN AGE

28:45.644 --> 28:47.396
WHEN MOST OF US
ARE STILL STARTING OUT

28:47.396 --> 28:48.727
IN OUR SPECIALITIES.

28:48.727 --> 28:50.689
I'D ASK ABOUT SOME
OF YOUR 20-ODD PUBLISHED PAPERS

28:50.689 --> 28:52.231
THAT I'VE READ.

28:52.231 --> 28:56.275
MOSTLY, I'D LIKE TO KNOW WHAT
THE HELL YOU'RE DOING RIGHT NOW.

28:56.275 --> 28:58.858
TRANS-AORTIC VALVE
REPLACEMENT.

28:58.858 --> 29:00.820
BY NOT PUTTING HER ON BYPASS,

29:00.820 --> 29:02.411
I TURN YOUR SIX-HOUR PROCEDURE
INTO --

29:02.411 --> 29:05.534
INTO A ONE-HOUR PROCEDURE.
BRILLIANT.

29:05.534 --> 29:06.956
BLOODY BRILLIANT.

29:06.956 --> 29:09.328
LOOK, IT MAY SEEM LIKE
BAILEY HIRED ME ON A WHIM,

29:09.328 --> 29:11.250
BUT I DON'T DO ANYTHING
ON A WHIM.

29:11.250 --> 29:13.422
I LIKE TO CHOOSE
THE PEOPLE THAT I WORK FOR.

29:13.422 --> 29:16.425
[ INTRO TO RHODES' "THE LAKES"
PLAYS ]

29:19.378 --> 29:20.469
WHEN --
[ SIGHS ]

29:20.469 --> 29:22.221
WHEN WILSON TOLD ME
THAT YOU LIED...

29:22.221 --> 29:26.806
ABOUT, UH,
BEING SICK...

29:29.098 --> 29:30.479
...I BELIEVED HER.

29:30.479 --> 29:32.101
MM-HMM.

29:35.104 --> 29:36.445
YOU DIDN'T THINK
THAT THAT --

29:36.445 --> 29:38.157
THAT THAT WAS WHAT?

29:38.157 --> 29:42.822
THAT I...SIDED WITH HER
BECAUSE...

29:42.822 --> 29:45.574
NO.

29:45.574 --> 29:47.827
GOOD. GOOD.

29:47.827 --> 29:50.329
I MEAN, IT CROSSED MY MIND,
BUT NO.

29:50.329 --> 29:52.912
IT CROSSED YOUR MIND?

29:52.912 --> 29:54.213
YEAH, OF COURSE IT DID.

29:54.213 --> 29:55.794
I MEAN,
IT'S ALWAYS A POSSIBILITY.

29:55.794 --> 29:58.087
IT'S ALWAYS THERE.

29:58.087 --> 30:00.469
BUT IT WASN'T.

30:00.469 --> 30:02.631
WHA-- WITH ME --
YOU HAVE TO KNOW --

30:02.631 --> 30:04.473
HEY, DR. SHEPHERD...

30:04.473 --> 30:05.724
♪ THE LAKE ♪

30:05.724 --> 30:07.306
WE ARE GOOD.

30:07.306 --> 30:14.143
♪ SUMMER WILL FIND US THERE
WAITING ♪

30:14.143 --> 30:17.486
♪ WE CAN SEE THROUGH THE SHADOWS
WITH LIGHT ♪

30:17.486 --> 30:22.321
♪ TO BE WHERE WE BELONG ♪

30:22.321 --> 30:26.075
♪ WE CAN BE SAFE
IN OUR OWN LITTLE PLACE ♪

30:26.075 --> 30:29.498
♪ WHERE THE SKYLINE KISS
THE SHORE ♪

30:29.498 --> 30:32.411
♪ WE WILL GO ON ♪

30:32.411 --> 30:35.754
♪ WE WILL GO ON AND ON ♪

30:39.588 --> 30:43.172
♪ WE FEEL ALIVE IN THE WATERS
WITH DIVERS ♪

30:43.172 --> 30:47.596
♪ THE NIGHT FIRE WARMS
OUR BONES ♪

30:47.596 --> 30:52.972
♪ WE WILL GO ALL,
WE WILL GO ON AND ON ♪

30:54.813 --> 30:56.355
BLAKE.

30:56.355 --> 31:01.820
♪ MY LOVE,
THERE'S NOTHING ELSE WE CAN DO ♪

31:01.820 --> 31:05.154
♪ AND I STILL HAVE FAITH
IN YOU ♪

31:05.154 --> 31:07.196
OKAY.
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

31:07.196 --> 31:08.487
YOU WANT TO STAND
IN THE CORNER

31:08.487 --> 31:10.449
WHILE I ATTACH THE HOLY GRAIL
OF KIDNEYS, BE MY GUEST.

31:10.449 --> 31:12.331
NO, NO.
OKAY.

31:12.331 --> 31:14.703
SO LET'S GIVE WILSON A BREAK,
AND STEP ON IN HERE.

31:14.703 --> 31:16.875
♪ WE CAN SEE THROUGH THE SHADOWS
WITH LIGHT ♪

31:16.875 --> 31:19.548
♪ TO BE WHERE WE BELONG ♪

31:19.548 --> 31:21.260
I'VE PREPARED THE VESSELS
FOR ANASTOMOSIS,

31:21.260 --> 31:23.923
AND I LIKE AN END-TO-END
WITH THE INTERNAL ILIAC.

31:23.923 --> 31:27.596
♪ WE CAN BE SAFE
IN OUR OWN LITTLE PLACE ♪

31:27.596 --> 31:30.099
GIVE ME SOME ROOM HERE.
GET BACK.

31:31.890 --> 31:34.063
SO, WANT TO TELL ME
WHY YOU MISSED THE CHECKS?

31:34.063 --> 31:36.145
DR. KAREV WARNED ME

31:36.145 --> 31:38.437
TO STEER CLEAR OF THE KID'S MOM,
AND I DIDN'T,

31:38.437 --> 31:39.608
AND SHE SORT OF JUMPED ME.

31:39.608 --> 31:41.570
SHE'S A DOC KNOCKER.

31:41.570 --> 31:42.982
THAT'S A THING?

31:42.982 --> 31:44.573
IT IS VERY MUCH A THING.

31:44.573 --> 31:45.694
H-HOW DID HE SEE THAT?

31:45.694 --> 31:48.787
I SWEAR I JUST SAW A NICE,
SCARED MOM.

31:48.787 --> 31:50.739
LET ME TELL YOU
WHAT KAREV SAW.

31:50.739 --> 31:51.790
A CONCERNED MOM

31:51.790 --> 31:54.243
WITH A KID WHO TAKES
A LOT OF ENERGY

31:54.243 --> 31:55.995
AND A HUSBAND WHO ONLY
LOOKS UP FROM HIS PHONE

31:55.995 --> 31:57.496
TO CONTRADICT
EVERYTHING THAT SHE SAYS.

31:57.496 --> 32:00.629
A MOM WHO WAS PRESENTED
WITH A DOCTOR

32:00.629 --> 32:04.093
WHO WAS ONLY INTERESTED
IN HER SON'S WELL-BEING.

32:04.093 --> 32:06.175
MADE HER FEEL GOOD,
TAKEN CARE OF.

32:06.175 --> 32:08.307
SUCTION.

32:08.307 --> 32:10.759
I DIDN'T SEE THAT.
OF COURSE NOT.

32:10.759 --> 32:12.051
YOU'VE ONLY BEEN A DOCTOR
FOR FIVE MINUTES.

32:12.051 --> 32:13.472
BUT YOU'LL LEARN.

32:13.472 --> 32:14.974
PEOPLE AREN'T ALWAYS
WHO YOU THINK THEY ARE.

32:14.974 --> 32:17.766
YOU LEARN TO SEE THROUGH IT.
YOU LEARN FAST.

32:17.766 --> 32:19.148
OH, THERE IT IS.

32:19.148 --> 32:20.439
RIGHT THERE.

32:20.439 --> 32:22.191
YOU WANT TO GET IT?

32:22.191 --> 32:24.443
♪ WE WILL GO ON AND ON ♪

32:24.443 --> 32:27.656
♪ WE WILL GO ON AND ON ♪

32:27.656 --> 32:29.158
CHIEF.

32:29.158 --> 32:31.490
LOOKS LIKE BOTH OF MR. JAFFEE'S
TRANSPLANTS WERE SUCCESSFUL.

32:31.490 --> 32:33.122
OH, GREAT NEWS!

32:33.122 --> 32:34.953
OH, DR. RIGGS.
HOW YOU SETTLING IN?

32:34.953 --> 32:37.246
WELL, YOU'D HAVE TO ASK
DR. PIERCE THAT, I THINK.
[ CHUCKLES ]

32:37.246 --> 32:38.877
WELL,
HAVE YOU MET EVERYBODY?

32:38.877 --> 32:40.919
UM, DR. NATHAN RIGGS,

32:40.919 --> 32:42.081
THIS IS GREY, SHEPHERD,
THIS IS HUNT.

32:42.081 --> 32:43.172
NICE TO MEET YOU.
RIGGS.

32:43.172 --> 32:45.294
HUNT!
HEY.

32:47.756 --> 32:50.179
YEAH, WE, UM...

32:50.179 --> 32:52.091
DR. HUNT AND I
GO BACK A BIT.

32:52.091 --> 32:54.593
OH!
OH, I DIDN'T REALIZE.

32:54.593 --> 32:56.145
NO.
NO [SCOFFS] YOU DIDN'T.

32:56.145 --> 32:56.855
MAYBE YOU SHOULD'VE
ASKED AROUND

32:56.855 --> 32:59.228
BEFORE YOU DECIDED TO BRING

32:59.228 --> 33:01.100
A COMPLETE STRANGER
INTO THE HOSPITAL.

33:01.100 --> 33:02.941
ALL RIGHT, OWEN,
WHY DON'T YOU AND I JUST --

33:02.941 --> 33:04.483
DID YOU THINK
THIS WAS HOW IT WAS DONE?

33:04.483 --> 33:06.775
DIDN'T YOU THINK
FOR ONE SECOND

33:06.775 --> 33:08.367
THAT,
AS CHIEF OF THIS HOSPITAL,

33:08.367 --> 33:10.569
IT IS YOUR RESPONSIBILITY
TO VET YOUR PEOPLE?

33:10.569 --> 33:12.821
'CAUSE THIS --
THIS IS A BAD CALL, BAILEY.

33:12.821 --> 33:14.823
THIS IS A REALLY BAD CALL.

33:14.823 --> 33:17.036
AND IT WAS THOUGHTLESS,
AND IT WAS RECKLESS --
HUNT.

33:18.327 --> 33:21.830
WHY DON'T WE GO TO MY OFFICE
AND TALK ABOUT THIS?

33:21.830 --> 33:23.882
♪♪

33:33.972 --> 33:35.724
WHAT'S DONE IS DONE,
RIGHT?

33:42.691 --> 33:45.144
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

33:50.989 --> 33:52.531
[ SIREN WAILS IN DISTANCE ]

33:52.531 --> 33:55.204
[ SIGHS ]

33:57.366 --> 33:58.497
WHAT DID HE SAY?

33:58.497 --> 34:00.829
NOTHING.

34:00.829 --> 34:04.333
WHATEVER THIS IS...

34:04.333 --> 34:05.464
HE'S NOT TALKING.

34:07.876 --> 34:09.508
[ SIGHS ]
MEREDITH...

34:09.508 --> 34:12.721
♪♪

34:15.974 --> 34:17.726
I MADE A PROMISE
TO CRISTINA

34:17.726 --> 34:20.018
THAT I WOULDN'T LET YOU
GO DARK AND TWISTY,

34:20.018 --> 34:22.811
THAT I'D BE YOUR PERSON
IF YOU NEEDED ONE.

34:22.811 --> 34:26.445
I DON'T WANT TO TALK.

34:26.445 --> 34:27.736
OKAY.

34:27.736 --> 34:29.067
YOU DON'T HAVE TO.

34:29.067 --> 34:31.900
BUT JUST TELL ME --
DO WE HATE HIM?

34:38.867 --> 34:41.250
WE HATE HIM.

34:43.081 --> 34:44.123
OKAY, THEN.
WE HATE HIM.

34:54.383 --> 34:57.346
SO, UM,
HOW'D IT GO LAST NIGHT?

34:57.346 --> 34:59.478
UGH.
IT DIDN'T.

34:59.478 --> 35:02.601
I MEAN, DINNER WAS GREAT.
IT WAS FUN, ACTUALLY.

35:02.601 --> 35:04.563
BUT WHEN IT WAS FINALLY TIME
TO HAVE THE REAL TALK,

35:04.563 --> 35:06.024
APRIL GOT PAGED.

35:06.024 --> 35:07.396
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

35:07.396 --> 35:09.898
HONESTLY, I THINK WE WERE BOTH
TRYING TO AVOID THE SUBJECT,

35:09.898 --> 35:11.280
BUT...

35:11.280 --> 35:13.402
YEAH, I NEED TO HAVE SEX
WITH MY WIFE.

35:13.402 --> 35:15.574
AND THAT CAN'T HAPPEN
WITH YOU IN MY HOUSE.

35:15.574 --> 35:16.695
NOW, YOU'RE IN A BAD PLACE.

35:16.695 --> 35:18.197
I GET THAT.

35:18.197 --> 35:20.038
AND I WILL DO ANYTHING
I CAN TO -- I-I WILL.

35:20.038 --> 35:22.621
BUT I NEED YOU OFF MY SOFA.

35:22.621 --> 35:23.502
I MEAN, IT'S FOR THE GOOD
OF THE HOSPITAL --

35:23.502 --> 35:25.954
TOTALLY GET IT.
OKAY?

35:25.954 --> 35:27.956
I'LL SEE YOU.
ALL RIGHT.

35:27.956 --> 35:30.919
[ SIGHS ]

35:30.919 --> 35:33.252
I MEAN,
HOW DID HE SEEM TO YOU?

35:33.252 --> 35:35.304
RIGGS?
YEAH.

35:35.304 --> 35:39.308
I DON'T KNOW.
SMART, CAPABLE, CHARMING.

35:39.308 --> 35:40.559
UGH.

35:40.559 --> 35:43.472
I THINK BAILEY WAS RIGHT.

35:43.472 --> 35:45.764
OWEN WOULDN'T
TELL YOU ANYTHING?

35:45.764 --> 35:48.897
HE JUST SHUT ME OUT.
I DON'T KNOW WHY.

35:48.897 --> 35:52.771
AND THEN...I'M AFRAID
I MIGHT'VE BEEN RACIST.

35:52.771 --> 35:53.982
[ SIGHS ]
GOD, I HATE THIS DAY.

35:53.982 --> 35:56.405
OKAY.
OKAY, BACK IT UP.

35:56.405 --> 35:59.157
OH, GOOD!
I CAN TALK TO YOU ABOUT THIS.

35:59.157 --> 36:02.331
I AM WORRIED
I OFFENDED EDWARDS.

36:02.331 --> 36:03.332
I NEED YOU TO TELL ME.

36:03.332 --> 36:05.994
WHY ME?
'CAUSE I'M YOUR SISTER?

36:05.994 --> 36:07.626
YES.

36:07.626 --> 36:08.917
OR BECAUSE
I'M YOUR "SISTAH"?

36:08.917 --> 36:10.379
NO.

36:10.379 --> 36:12.130
THIS IS EXACTLY
WHAT I WAS WORRIED ABOUT.

36:12.130 --> 36:13.632
OKAY.
WHAT DO YOU THINK
YOU DID?

36:13.632 --> 36:17.796
I DON'T THINK I DID ANYTHING,
BUT I THINK SHE THINKS I DID.

36:17.796 --> 36:20.559
AMELIA, USE YOUR WORDS.

36:20.559 --> 36:21.600
DID WHAT?

36:21.600 --> 36:22.971
[ SIGHS ]

36:22.971 --> 36:26.104
SIDED WITH WILSON OVER HER
BECAUSE SHE'S BLACK.

36:26.104 --> 36:28.727
WHICH I DIDN'T DO.
I THINK.

36:28.727 --> 36:32.731
I -- GOD, I-I HATE THAT THIS IS
EVEN AN ISSUE ALL OF A SUDDEN.

36:32.731 --> 36:35.984
WELL,
IT'S NOT AN ISSUE FOR YOU.

36:35.984 --> 36:38.317
AND IT'S NOT
ALL OF A SUDDEN.

36:38.317 --> 36:39.658
I MEAN, OKAY,

36:39.658 --> 36:41.240
IT'S NOT "MISSISSIPPI BURNING"
OR ANYTHING,

36:41.240 --> 36:44.583
BUT IT IS ALL OVER.

36:44.583 --> 36:46.915
IT'S WHEN PEOPLE ASSUME
I'M A NURSE.

36:46.915 --> 36:49.628
OR WHEN I GO
TO GET ON AN AIRPLANE

36:49.628 --> 36:51.460
WITH MY FIRST-CLASS TICKET,

36:51.460 --> 36:53.962
AND THEY TELL ME THAT
THEY'RE NOT BOARDING COACH YET.

36:53.962 --> 36:56.425
IT'S LIKE A LOW BUZZ
IN THE BACKGROUND.

36:56.425 --> 36:58.046
AND SOMETIMES
YOU DON'T EVEN NOTICE IT,

36:58.046 --> 37:00.599
AND SOMETIMES
IT'S LOUD AND ANNOYING.

37:00.599 --> 37:04.393
AND SOMETIMES
IT CAN GET DANGEROUS.

37:04.393 --> 37:08.056
AND SOMETIMES IT IS RIDICULOUS,
LIKE RIGHT NOW.

37:08.056 --> 37:09.608
BUT IT'S NOT FUNNY.

37:09.608 --> 37:11.650
I MEAN, IF I'M DOING IT
AND I DON'T EVEN NOTICE IT --

37:11.650 --> 37:12.981
THEN NOTICE IT.

37:14.483 --> 37:16.945
LOOK, DID EDWARDS TELL YOU
THAT SHE'S OKAY?

37:16.945 --> 37:19.358
YES.

37:19.358 --> 37:21.660
OKAY.

37:21.660 --> 37:24.743
THEN DON'T GIVE HER
THE EXTRA WORK

37:24.743 --> 37:26.665
OF HAVING TO MAKE YOU
FEEL GOOD ABOUT IT.

37:26.665 --> 37:29.127
RIGHT.

37:32.751 --> 37:34.463
OKAY, BUT HOW DO I KNOW
THAT SHE'S REALLY --

37:34.463 --> 37:37.876
BECAUSE SHE KNOWS YOU,
OKAY?

37:37.876 --> 37:41.139
SO LISTEN TO THE WORDS
THAT ARE COMING OUT OF HER MOUTH

37:41.139 --> 37:42.220
AND BELIEVE THEM.

37:42.220 --> 37:43.932
THIS IS NOT A SMALL THING.

37:46.345 --> 37:48.437
AND I'M GLAD THAT YOU FEEL LIKE
YOU CAN TALK TO ME ABOUT IT,

37:48.437 --> 37:50.389
BUT...

37:50.389 --> 37:52.521
I-I DON'T SPEAK
FOR ALL BLACK PEOPLE.

37:52.521 --> 37:55.394
I AM NOT THE SPOKESWOMAN.
NO ONE IS.

37:55.394 --> 38:00.449
AND IT IS KIND OF ANNOYING
TO BE ASKED QUESTIONS LIKE I AM.

38:00.449 --> 38:05.113
BUT, UM, ONE PIECE OF ADVICE
THAT I CAN GIVE YOU

38:05.113 --> 38:06.705
THAT I THINK
WE WOULD ALL AGREE WITH

38:06.705 --> 38:12.581
IS THAT IF YOU FEEL
UNCOMFORTABLE HAVING DONE IT,

38:12.581 --> 38:16.505
CHECK YOUR WHITE PRIVILEGE,
AND DON'T DO IT AGAIN.

38:19.548 --> 38:22.511
BUT I DON'T THINK
YOU'RE RACIST.

38:22.511 --> 38:25.884
YOU DON'T THINK?

38:25.884 --> 38:28.597
GIRL, GET IN THE CAR.

38:28.597 --> 38:30.639
OKAY.

38:32.351 --> 38:35.233
♪♪

38:38.026 --> 38:39.358
[ LAUGHTER ]

38:46.785 --> 38:49.077
HE HAD SO MANY GRANDKIDS
I LOST COUNT.

38:49.077 --> 38:50.869
[ LAUGHS ]
I'M NOT EXAGGERATING.

38:50.869 --> 38:52.541
SEVEN.

38:52.541 --> 38:55.414
HE HAD SEVEN GRANDCHILDREN
FROM SIX KIDS,

38:55.414 --> 38:57.836
WHO HE RAISED ON HIS OWN
AFTER HIS WIFE DIED.

38:57.836 --> 39:00.168
ARE YOU OKAY?

39:00.168 --> 39:03.762
I TREATED MR. JAFFEE FOR YEARS,

39:03.762 --> 39:06.515
AND I FINALLY GET HIM
WHAT HE NEEDS,

39:06.515 --> 39:09.227
AND YOU JUST COME AND TAKE IT
AND RUN WITH IT.

39:09.227 --> 39:13.602
AND I HELPED YOU ALL DAY.

39:16.184 --> 39:19.648
HE WAS MY PATIENT.

39:19.648 --> 39:20.819
THAT'S ALL.

39:20.819 --> 39:22.651
JO.

39:22.651 --> 39:26.405
♪ A BABY GIRL WITHOUT A HOME ♪

39:26.405 --> 39:28.326
♪ TRAGEDY'S REIGN
LEFT HER ALONE ♪

39:28.326 --> 39:30.869
SO, YOU WANT TO GRAB
A DRINK?

39:30.869 --> 39:34.082
♪ I GUESS I SHOULDA
KNOWN BETTER ♪

39:34.082 --> 39:35.494
YEAH.

39:35.494 --> 39:36.585
♪ I GUESS I SHOULDA
KNOWN BETTER ♪

39:36.585 --> 39:39.998
I WOULD LOVE THAT,
ACTUALLY.

39:39.998 --> 39:41.880
OKAY.
[ LAUGHS ]

39:41.880 --> 39:42.801
♪ PART OF THE REVOLUTION ♪

39:42.801 --> 39:46.094
[ SIGHS ]

39:46.094 --> 39:49.097
SO, UM,
WE'VE GOT SCIENCE COVERED.

39:49.097 --> 39:51.349
I'M STRONG ON HISTORY
AND GEOGRAPHY.

39:51.349 --> 39:52.811
UH, HOW'S YOUR
POPULAR CULTURE?

39:52.811 --> 39:54.392
I JUST WANT TO GET A SENSE
OF OUR STRENGTHS HERE --

39:54.392 --> 39:56.515
RICHARD, I'M SORRY.

39:56.515 --> 39:58.186
I'M HERE TO --

39:58.186 --> 40:00.899
I WANTED TO HAVE --
I'M TRYING TO...

40:00.899 --> 40:02.320
I'M HERE TO MEET GIRLS.

40:02.320 --> 40:04.232
I DON'T CARE ABOUT TRIVIA.

40:04.232 --> 40:05.524
I DON'T EVEN LIKE TRIVIA.

40:05.524 --> 40:07.736
OH.

40:07.736 --> 40:09.488
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS,
LAUGHTER ]

40:09.488 --> 40:12.160
I SEE.

40:12.160 --> 40:13.702
THAT'S...

40:13.702 --> 40:16.034
AND THEN YOU OFFERED TO COME,
AND I DIDN'T KNOW HOW TO SAY NO.

40:16.034 --> 40:18.667
AND I JUST -- I DIDN'T WANT
TO GO IT ALONE, HONESTLY.

40:18.667 --> 40:21.379
IT'S JUST IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME,
AND I'M RUSTY AND NERVOUS.

40:21.379 --> 40:23.341
AND I FEEL LIKE I LIVED
AN ENTIRE LIFETIME

40:23.341 --> 40:25.093
SINCE THE LAST TIME
I DATED,

40:25.093 --> 40:26.845
AND I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHERE TO START.

40:26.845 --> 40:28.807
YOU NEED A WINGMAN.

40:30.549 --> 40:32.350
WHAT DO YOU LIKE?

40:32.350 --> 40:33.892
GLASSES?

40:33.892 --> 40:35.894
CARDIGAN.
SHE HAS A NICE LAUGH.

40:35.894 --> 40:37.976
YOU INTO TATTOOS?

40:39.267 --> 40:41.359
♪ PART OF THE REVOLUTION ♪

40:41.359 --> 40:42.861
NOT THAT MANY TATTOOS.

40:42.861 --> 40:44.362
WELL, YOU KNOW,
I-I'M JUST TRYING

40:44.362 --> 40:46.154
TO GET A SENSE
OF WHAT WE'RE AFTER HERE.

40:46.154 --> 40:48.737
♪ WE WON'T ACCEPT EXCUSES ♪

40:48.737 --> 40:50.949
GLASSES IS CUTE.

40:50.949 --> 40:52.701
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

40:52.701 --> 40:54.663
UH, SIT UP STRAIGHT.

40:57.786 --> 40:59.377
HELLO, LADIES.

40:59.377 --> 41:02.040
IT'S HARD TO FIGHT
AGAINST CERTAIN BIASES.

41:02.040 --> 41:03.712
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

41:03.712 --> 41:06.715
IT'S IMPORTANT TO KEEP
AN OPEN MIND.

41:06.715 --> 41:08.386
IT'S HOW WE LEARN.

41:08.386 --> 41:10.759
IT'S HOW WE GROW.

41:10.759 --> 41:13.552
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]
IT'S HOW WE MOVE FORWARD.

41:13.552 --> 41:16.014
[ DOORS CLOSE ]
DR. GREY, RIGHT?

41:16.014 --> 41:17.856
YEP.

41:17.856 --> 41:20.058
YOURS IS EASY
TO REMEMBER.

41:20.058 --> 41:22.310
IT'S ON ALL
THE HOSPITAL STATIONERY.

41:24.603 --> 41:26.104
WHAT'S THE STORY THERE?

41:26.104 --> 41:28.867
THAT'S TOO LONG A STORY
TO TELL.

41:28.867 --> 41:31.159
♪ WE TOLERATE NO ABUSES ♪

41:32.611 --> 41:34.953
I WAS ACTUALLY HEADED
ACROSS THE STREET.

41:34.953 --> 41:36.785
I WAS GONNA GRAB A DRINK
OR SOMETHING.

41:36.785 --> 41:38.997
ARE YOU HEADED THAT WAY,
OR...?

41:38.997 --> 41:42.791
♪ WHY, WHY, WHY, WHY? ♪

41:42.791 --> 41:44.292
I'M A FRIEND
OF OWEN HUNT'S.

41:44.292 --> 41:46.755
UNTIL WE DON'T.

41:46.755 --> 41:48.587
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

41:48.587 --> 41:50.338
I SEE.

41:50.338 --> 41:52.510
SO, NO.

41:52.510 --> 41:55.393
♪ I GUESS I SHOULDA
KNOWN BETTER ♪

41:55.393 --> 41:57.095
UNTIL WE LET OUR BIAS
TAKE OVER.

41:58.346 --> 42:02.480
♪ I HAD THIS GREAT EPIPHANY ♪

42:02.480 --> 42:04.442
♪ AND RHYTHM NATION
WAS THE DREAM ♪

42:04.442 --> 42:06.404
UNTIL WE SUCCUMB

42:06.404 --> 42:09.027
TO WHAT FEELS RIGHT
OR GOOD

42:09.027 --> 42:10.949
OR SATISFYING IN THAT MOMENT.

42:10.949 --> 42:13.572
BECAUSE EVEN THEN,
DEEP DOWN INSIDE,

42:13.572 --> 42:18.246
WE USUALLY KNOW
WE'RE GOING TO REGRET IT.

42:18.246 --> 42:21.920
♪ I GUESS NEXT TIME
I'LL KNOW BETTER ♪
